# Axis 2 — multi-shot resume

The resume entry is invoked more than once from a single handler arm, and the
results are combined. This is the hard in-process capability: the captured
continuation must be reusable (N→M), not one-shot. The portable-VM reference
runner supports it today, and the Rust runner's multi-shot (R.6) has landed;
v2 JS does not yet implement `effect.*` — hence "runner order by measured spike".

```scalascript
multi effect Choose:
  def choose(): Boolean

def prog(): List[Int] =
  val b = Choose.choose()
  if b then List(1) else List(2)

val r = handle(prog()) {
  case Choose.choose(resume) => resume(true) ++ resume(false)
  case Return(x) => x
}
println(r)
```
